20:14.880 --> 20:16.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Your mouth is shut!

20:16.215 --> 20:17.183 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
RECRUITS: Aye, sir!

20:17.216 --> 20:21.187 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: I said, do you understand
me?.

20:21.220 --> 20:23.556 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
RECRUITS: Aye, sir!

20:23.589 --> 20:32.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: They now start
thirteen
weeks of grueling, disorienting,
physically

20:32.798 --> 20:35.201 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stressful training.

20:35.234 --> 20:39.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rebekah Wolff is one of the
young female recruits
who wants to join the fight to
go into one

20:39.538 --> 20:44.009 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the jobs that for generations
had been
blocked to women, until now.

20:44.043 --> 20:47.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Low-altitude air defense is what
she wants
to do.

20:47.313 --> 20:51.684 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's basically shooting
shoulder-fired Stinger
missiles at enemy aircraft.

20:51.717 --> 20:53.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's what you want to be
doing, shooting
Stinger missiles?

20:53.419 --> 20:54.386 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REBEKAH WOLFF, Marine Corps
Recruit: Yes.

20:54.420 --> 20:55.354 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Why that?

20:55.387 --> 20:56.922 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REBEKAH WOLFF: Because it'd be
cool.

20:56.956 --> 20:58.791 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

20:58.824 --> 21:03.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REBEKAH WOLFF: Not a lot of
females have had
that opportunity until now,
really, so that's

21:03.295 --> 21:04.396 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
exciting.

21:04.430 --> 21:07.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Of course,
that's a long
way off.

21:07.333 --> 21:12.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For now, she's not only got to
prove herself
at boot camp, but she will have
to pass tougher

21:12.238 --> 21:15.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
physical standards than females
have ever
had to meet before.

21:15.441 --> 21:21.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the first night, after
filling out some
paperwork, recruits are required
to make one

21:21.147 --> 21:22.982 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
phone call home.

21:23.015 --> 21:26.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: They're
instructed to shout
five scripted lines into the
phone, nothing

21:26.685 --> 21:27.653 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
more.

21:27.686 --> 21:29.321 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Thank you for your
support!

21:29.355 --> 21:31.257 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Goodbye for now!

21:31.290 --> 21:36.061 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Drill
instructors intentionally
create this sense of chaos, a
miniature fog

21:36.095 --> 21:37.763 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of war.

21:37.796 --> 21:43.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They want to see how the
recruits respond,
and to shake their civilian
mind-set.

21:43.068 --> 21:44.436 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SGT.

21:44.470 --> 21:47.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER DUKE, Marine Corps: We
need to break
them down mentally.

21:47.840 --> 21:51.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We need to break down these
individualities
that they come with of self and
me and I.

21:51.810 --> 21:56.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We need to break them down to
basically nothing,
so we can build them back up,
not as one,

21:56.048 --> 21:59.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but as one team, one element to
join our Marine
Corps.

21:59.185 --> 22:00.152 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's not my Marine Corps.

22:00.186 --> 22:01.153 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's not his Marine Corps.

22:01.187 --> 22:02.888 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's our Marine Corps.

22:02.922 --> 22:07.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: We first
caught up with
Rebekah Wolff earlier this
summer back home

22:07.293 --> 22:08.260 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in rural Maryland.

22:08.294 --> 22:11.096 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At the time, she was living with
her parents.

22:11.130 --> 22:15.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Her mom and dad didn't like it
that she was
joining the Marine Corps, but
they were not

22:15.100 --> 22:16.502 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
surprised.

22:16.535 --> 22:20.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From an early age, Rebekah
wanted to break
the traditional girl mold.

22:20.339 --> 22:24.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: When she was young, she
said she was
always going to drive
motorcycles, drink beer,

22:24.210 --> 22:25.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
smoke cigarettes, and get
tattoos.

22:25.411 --> 22:26.612 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

22:26.645 --> 22:28.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: I can remember her
telling me that,
oh, my goodness.

22:28.514 --> 22:32.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: How do you
feel about the
idea that your daughter might
end up in a

22:32.251 --> 22:34.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
combat unit, maybe on the front
lines somewhere?

22:34.553 --> 22:39.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SCOTT WOLFF, Father of Rebekah
Wolff: I don't
think any parent wants their
kid, boy or girl,

22:39.792 --> 22:42.261 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to go to combat.

22:42.294 --> 22:43.629 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I surely don't.

22:43.662 --> 22:47.132 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I feel that they shouldn't be on
the front
lines.

22:47.166 --> 22:51.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: I don't know that she
fully understands
what she's getting into, though,
too, sometimes.

22:51.637 --> 22:53.372 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, I mean, we have explained.

22:53.405 --> 22:55.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's like, well, I will be able
to shoot
helicopters.

22:55.374 --> 22:57.409 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Well, they do shoot back.

22:57.443 --> 22:59.144 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't know that she
comprehends that.

22:59.178 --> 23:01.046 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:01.080 --> 23:04.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Turns out the
Marine Corps
didn't want women in certain
combat jobs either.

23:04.950 --> 23:09.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 2013, the secretary of
defense ordered
that all combat positions be
opened to women.

23:09.255 --> 23:12.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But after a period of
deliberations, the Marines
asked for an exemption.

23:12.992 --> 23:17.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They argued that putting women
into the infantry
and to other combat jobs would
make the Marine

23:17.796 --> 23:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Corps a less effective fighting
force.

23:20.499 --> 23:25.704 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: General Robert
Neller is
the commandant of the Marine
Corps, the highest

23:25.738 --> 23:27.373 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
uniformed officer.

23:27.406 --> 23:32.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says the Corps' resistance
came from a
test the Marines ran back in
2014.

23:32.378 --> 23:37.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It took all-male units and units
that mixed
men and women, and then compared
their performance

23:38.017 --> 23:39.485 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in a series of combat drills.

23:39.518 --> 23:41.253 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

23:41.287 --> 23:41.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT NELLER, Marine Corps
Commandant: And
then we ran them through a very
physically

23:41.754 --> 23:42.721 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
demanding test.

23:42.755 --> 23:44.523 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I mean, it was hard.

23:44.556 --> 23:48.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there was data in there that
showed, in
the aggregate, that, in certain
things, mostly

23:48.661 --> 23:53.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in load-bearing and the most
physically demanding
tasks, that the teams that have
females integrated

23:53.632 --> 23:57.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in them didn't perform at the
same levels
as the all-male team.

23:57.436 --> 24:02.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The results
showed that
male-only teams moved faster,
especially with

24:02.408 --> 24:07.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
heavy loads, they fired at the
enemy more
often, hit their targets more
often, and evacuated

24:07.913 --> 24:10.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
casualties faster.

24:10.349 --> 24:14.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Integrated units, with men and
women, also
suffered more injuries.

24:14.620 --> 24:17.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Commandant Neller acknowledges
integrated
teams did have some advantages.

24:18.023 --> 24:19.525 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

24:19.558 --> 24:21.293 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT NELLER: We found that
integrated teams
did better in problem-solving.

24:21.327 --> 24:26.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why, as part of a team,
if we have
differences, any of us have
differences, it

24:26.598 --> 24:30.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can mitigated because the team
figures out,
OK, you're good at this, you do
this.

24:30.336 --> 24:32.037 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You're better at this, you focus
on this.

24:32.071 --> 24:36.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The test was
criticized
by many, including the
commandant's boss,

24:36.241 --> 24:42.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the secretary of the Navy,
because it compared
highly experienced,
combat-hardened men with

24:42.114 --> 24:43.916 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
far less experienced women.

24:43.949 --> 24:45.784 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: Hit him in the face!

24:45.818 --> 24:50.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But, still,
there are many
who say you don't need a study
to prove that

24:50.422 --> 24:52.691 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
men and women, physically, are
different.

24:52.725 --> 24:54.426 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

24:54.460 --> 24:57.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY REINWALD (RET.), Marine
Corps: You know,
the Marine Corps, we're not
idealists.

24:57.896 --> 24:59.198 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We're realists.

24:59.231 --> 25:01.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we know that there are
differences between
men and women.

25:01.967 --> 25:06.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I came in the Marine Corps,
I was 5'3'',
I was 110 pounds.

25:06.305 --> 25:11.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to be able to do the same
thing as my
counterpart, who was 6'1'', you
know, 180

25:11.910 --> 25:16.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pounds, lean, mean fighting
machine-type thing,
was just unrealistic, no matter
how good of

25:16.715 --> 25:18.450 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
shape I was in at the time.

25:18.484 --> 25:22.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Retired
Colonel Mary Reinwald
spent 27 years in the Marine
Corps.

25:22.554 --> 25:26.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She now edits "Leatherneck"
magazine, which
is geared to the Marine
community.

25:26.492 --> 25:30.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She thinks women just don't
belong in certain
combat jobs because they're too
physically

25:30.963 --> 25:31.930 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
demanding.

25:31.964 --> 25:33.799 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

25:33.832 --> 25:35.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY REINWALD: I have no problem
saying I'm
not as physically strong as my
male counterpart.

25:35.701 --> 25:39.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I will also say that I bring
other things
to the table that he doesn't.

25:39.405 --> 25:40.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We can wish all we want.

25:40.706 --> 25:43.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But that doesn't mean that
everybody's going
to be the same.

25:43.175 --> 25:47.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The Marines'
attempt to
keep women from certain combat
jobs was rejected

25:47.579 --> 25:53.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by the defense secretary last
December, and
so now women can apply for all
combat positions

25:53.152 --> 25:58.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the Marine Corps, women like
18-year-old
Lacey Elkins.

25:58.390 --> 26:02.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's from Hays, Kansas, and
she's just three
weeks from finishing boot camp.

26:02.761 --> 26:05.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's applied to operate tanks
or amphibious
assault vehicles.

26:05.998 --> 26:08.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LACEY ELKINS, Marine Corps
Recruit: College
sounded boring.

26:08.967 --> 26:10.736 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Marine Corps offered me a
bigger challenge.

26:10.769 --> 26:12.037 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My brother is a Marine.

26:12.070 --> 26:13.806 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's in Africa right now.

26:13.839 --> 26:17.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It just offered me a bigger
challenge that
I was willing to accept and push
me outside

26:17.075 --> 26:18.043 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
my comfort zone.

26:18.076 --> 26:21.280 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what I was looking
for.

26:21.313 --> 26:23.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: I don't know a
lot of 18-year-olds
who ever say, I want to get
pushed out of

26:23.782 --> 26:24.917 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
my comfort zone.

26:24.950 --> 26:26.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You were really looking for a
challenge like
this?

26:26.685 --> 26:29.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LACEY ELKINS: Yes, sir.

26:29.121 --> 26:34.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Having the opportunity to be a
part of that
generation for women was
something that I

26:34.193 --> 26:37.529 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
wanted to do.

26:37.563 --> 26:41.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My dad, I think I nearly gave
him a heart
attack, because he started
screaming on the

26:41.700 --> 26:42.835 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
phone.

26:42.868 --> 26:44.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Screaming in a
good way
or a bad way?

26:44.303 --> 26:48.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LACEY ELKINS: No, he was like,
no, no, don't
even think about it..

26:48.574 --> 26:52.077 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
Twenty-one-year-old Victoria
Golab-Meyer comes from Sheridan,
Wyoming,

26:52.110 --> 26:56.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and she too wants to serve in
combat as a
combat engineer.

26:56.114 --> 27:01.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We caught up with her as she was
on the Crucible,
the grueling two-day 45-mile
course that's

27:01.920 --> 27:05.157 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the last major training event
for every Marine
recruit.

27:05.190 --> 27:08.293 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VICTORIA GOLAB-MEYER, Marine
Corps Recruit:
I want to be here.

27:08.327 --> 27:10.429 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I want to be fighting for my
country.

27:10.462 --> 27:12.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I want to learn how to be
honorable.

27:12.498 --> 27:14.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I want to learn to fight.

27:14.333 --> 27:19.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to advance my career and
be in a place
that feels like family.

27:19.171 --> 27:21.306 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know that they have your
back.

27:21.340 --> 27:25.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Part of what
sets the Marines
apart is how it trains recruits.

27:25.377 --> 27:31.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the rappel tower, at the
shooting range,
in mock combat, even in the
classrooms, the

27:31.650 --> 27:33.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sexes are divided.

27:33.252 --> 27:35.754 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Women train with women, men with
men.

27:35.787 --> 27:38.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Marines are the only service
that does
it this way.

27:38.690 --> 27:39.658 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SGT.

27:39.691 --> 27:40.659 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JENNIFER DUKE: One, it's just a
tradition.

27:40.692 --> 27:42.127 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's what the Marine Corps has
always done.

27:42.160 --> 27:43.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It takes away distraction.

27:43.161 --> 27:44.563 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most of these kids are high
school age.

27:44.596 --> 27:46.064 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, they're 18, 19 years
old.

27:46.098 --> 27:49.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, when you kind of get
down to boys
and girls, it's a distraction.

27:49.601 --> 27:53.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But others,
like retired
Lieutenant Colonel Kate Germano,
say this

27:53.805 --> 27:57.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
separation of the sexes is a bad
idea that
hurts females.

27:57.142 --> 27:58.110 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
LT.

27:58.143 --> 27:59.912 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

27:59.945 --> 28:02.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATE GERMANO (RET.), Marine
Corps: History
has shown that regardless of
where or when,

28:02.314 --> 28:04.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
separate is never equal.

28:04.182 --> 28:06.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that is absolutely evident
on Parris Island.

28:06.618 --> 28:10.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Germano
commanded the female
battalion at Parris Island, but
she was fired

28:10.622 --> 28:15.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in 2015, accused of creating a
